                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCellHeading">My First Blog Entry ... Ever!</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" class="TableCellHeading">
                        <p align="right"><i>By James Flowers,
                              4 June 2004</i></p>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCell">OK. A blog. Yikes! Well, while I'm not new to the Internet, I am a blog-newbie, so please excuse me while I settle in here.
                        *smile*
                        
                        <p>I guess the purpose of these entries is several-fold:</p>
                        
                        <p>1) To keep you all in touch with what's happening as we develop (or redevelop) various products for Earthdawn.</p>
                        
                        <p>2) To provide a means for me to post in just one place, thus centralizing "things" and hopefully avoid "forum-skipping" --
                           that's where I visit all the forums I can and post bits and pieces all over the Web.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>3) Giving you an insight into who I am, how I think, how I work, what non-Earthdawn or un-RedBrick stuff I'm doing, other
                           personal stuff; that sort of thing.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>With that in mind, I'll do my best to keep up regular postings here. If there's anything you want to direct to my attention,
                           then please email me at: jflowers@redbrick.co.nz -- I don't bite. Or use the Forums on this site; that way if there's a question
                           or comment that might be of interest to others, then I can answer for everyone to see!
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>Ciao fir niao, J;)</p>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
